en_324363_0	More than 60 Army personnel of Kopay-based 51 Division Headquarters under the Security Force Headquarters - Jaffna (SFHQ-J) on account of the forthcoming 23rd anniversary of the 51 Division Headquarters voluntarily donated their blood for use of patients in the North on Friday (17).
en_324363_1	This was the first project, the precursor to several other anniversary programmes that will come into effect, beginning on the anniversary day (August 24) on the directions of Major General Roshan Seneviratne, General Officer Commanding, 51 Division.
en_324363_2	The blood donation project was supported by a team of medical officers at the Jaffna Teaching Hospital and nursing staff.
